      "message": "Removed isHTML. Really what this code wants is a sum type, but Go doesn\u0027t have sum types. :-)\n\nI think keeping template.HTML is still valuable because that means the type checker will help enforce that escaping only happens once. It also helps document that the repl functions are supposed to produce trusted HTML.\n\nYou\u0027re right that, in practice, this just sticks casts everywhere, since most functions in html/template that should return template.HTML don\u0027t. But I would argue it still provides value. The casts are the places to pay close attention to in review.\n\nThoughts?",
