    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "14ac9af4_cc3f1386",
        "filename": "milo/frontend/middleware.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 198,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-25T21:23:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i see. i think the \"chunks can\u0027t be processed twice\" is the problem we should solve. It means that linkfiers are not composable and it will get worse with more linkifiers.\n\ncan we not mark things as processed if we cannot actually process them? i think this can be achieved by doing the following\n- change formatChunk: str is the original text. html is processed str. If html is empty, it means str is not processed yet. This means the \"At most one of str or html will be non-empty. That one is the field in use.\" complexity can be removed.\n- change repl in replaceAllInChunks from (func(string) template.HTML) to (func(formatChunk) []*formatChunk). \n\nwith this design, the bug repl does not have to call chunksToHTML in the end, but just return sChunks. Then we do chunks-to-html only in the very end of formatCommitDesc, and since that\u0027s the only callsite, it can be inlined.\n\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "2e30d9fc_be7215d8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 197,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 198,
        "endChar": 35
      },
      "revId": "9ee12bedfbff9d6dbedcf5cb4890e99974df48e3",
